\begin{abstract}
It is shown that the conclusion of the paper ``Hidden assumptions in
decoherence theory" \cite{vecchi} is the result of a misunderstanding of
the concept of pointer states. It is argued that pointer states are
{\em selected} by the interaction of quantum systems with the environment,
and are not based on any {\em measurement} by a conscious observer.

\end{abstract}
